thread.title_full: State police: Shots fired at driver in Wrentham | Boston Herald

author: Laurel J. Sweet
title: State police: Shots fired at driver in Wrentham
text:
State police this morning are hunting a suspect who fired at a man driving late last night on Route 495 south in Wrentham.
The driver was not injured, and state police spokesman David Procopio said police do not believe the assault was random.
The incident occurred shortly before 11 p.m.
Procopio said troopers have recovered "apparent ballistics evidence" from the vehicle that was allegedly fired upon.
They are seeking a car from which they believe the shots were fired.
No description was released.
